review_blob: Light and cloudy, little to no head. Aroma is of apples and wine. Very dry, under carbonated. Picking up fruity phenols. To me it seems that it was fermented at to high a temp, dried out and they had to under carb it so as to make it not overly dry.
Arrived hazy pale yellow.  Strong banana aroma.  This one is a banana bomb.  Initial taste is sweet, low carbonation and heavy.  I would categorize it as an imperial Belgian wheat beer.

Pours a murky medium amber with virtually no head.  Aroma is mainly overpowering alcohol (whiskey), hints of vanilla something else I cant place.  Flavor starts heavily sweet, moderately bitter and finishes the same.  Alcohol dominates the flavor, then makes way for a wheat malt flavor then oak, which all comes off as a coconut flavor. Medium bodied, oily but lively carbonated.   I would sum it up as coconut flavored whiskey.

Pours Medium amber with a fully diminishing white head. Aroma is heavily malty, bread, cookies, grain (crystal malts) hints of caramel.   Flavor is well balanced, crystal malt flavor throughout (60-80 lovibond)  which makes it somewhat one dimensional.  Body is light with a dry finish.  Lively carbonation.

pours hazy medium orange with a creamy off-white head. Aroma is slightly malty of cookies, heavily hoppy of pine, grapefruit and lemon. heavily yeasty of leather , apples and cherries.  Flavor is well balanced for an IPA, nice nutty malty backbone, piny and citrys hops dominate.  Medium to full bodied, creamy and softly carbonated, light alcohol in the finish.
beer_name: Dark Horse Double Crooked Tree IPA

review_blob: Pours clear light yellow with a large fizzy white head.  Aroma is moderately malty, of hay, light bread, straw. moderately hoppy of herbs and lemons.  Nicly balanced twords bitter, nice and light, hop finish was more bitter. Light to medium body, watery and soft co2.

Pours bark amber/red with a fizzy light-brown head.  Aroma is heavily malt driven, of grain and toasted malts, lightly yeasty, dough, grapes, pear and cherries.  Flavor is balanced twords sweet, toasty, malty, carmel/tofee.  Medium bodied, watery, and almost flat.
beer_name: Dark Horse Scotty Karate Scotch Ale

review_blob: pours muddy black with a large head.  Aroma is heavily malty of roasted malts, dark chocolate and strong coffee.  Flavor is bitter, roasty, and a bit ashy.  medium to full bodied, creamy and softly carbonated.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: pours hazy medium yellow with a creamy head.  Aroma is lightly malty and hoppy, with yeast being dominate; horse blanket and soap, hints of apple and coriander.  Flavor is well balanced, slightly yeasty, spicy with citrus bitterness.  Dry clean refreshing finish.  light to medium bodied, creamy and lively.

Pours dark black with a small froth head. Aroma is malty consisting of dark bread, roasted malts, and carmel.  lightly hoppy and yeasty.  Flavor is well balanced and complex. roasted malts, hints of burnt carmel, and toffee. Full bodied, creamy and softly carbonated.

pours muddy black with a creamy light-brown head.  Aroma is malty of cookies and roasted malts, lightly hoppy and lightly yeasty.  Flavor has a great balance, roasted malts, carmel with a firm bitterness and a clean finish. Full bodied creamy and softly carbonated, Best of the series so far.
beer_name: Lagunitas Cruising with Ruben and The Jets

review_blob: Pours hazy medium orange with a fizzy off-white head.  Aroma is moderately malty of grain and carmel, moderately hoppy of pine, resin and lime. Flavor is balanced twords bitter starts sweetish, grainy, biscuity and finishes more bitter, citrus, lemon.  Medium to full bodied, creamy and livley. Nice

pours medium brown with a rocky off-white head.  Aroma: moderately malty of cookies, heavily hoppy of pine, oranges and lime.  Flavor starts lightly sweet, and heavily bitter, great hop flavor, piny and citrus and alcohol sweetness. Medium bodied and creamy with livley Co2.

Pours medium orange with a frothy off-white head.  Aroma is lightly malty; cookies, toasted malts. lightly hoppy, and lightly yeasty; dough and leather.  Flavor starts balanced twords bitter and clean with hop bitters, finishes with some carmel malts flavor and sharper bitterness but clean.  Light to medium bodied, creamy and softly carbonated

Pours dark brown with a frothy light brown head.  Aroma is moderatly malty of cookies, lightly hoppy piney notes, lightly yeaty maybe bananas and definatly coffee.  Flavor is well balanced with espresso roast and crystal carmel malts, heavily bitter and slightly burnt flavors.  Medium bodied, oily and lively carbonated.

Pours dark redish brown with a frothy light brown head.  Aroma is moderatly malty of toasted bread and grain, lightly hoppy and heavy yeast notes of grape, cherry, red wine.  Flavor starts balanced twords sweet, complex dark fruit and cherry flavors dominate.  Finishes a bit sweeter yet.  Medium bodied, creamy and softly carbonated.

Flavor starts with a great balance, hoppy for a porter, grassy, and roasted malts, dark coffee, chocolate and dark fruits.  Medium bodied, oily and softly carbonated.

Pours clear dark red with a fizzy light brown.  Aroma is lightly malty, heavily hoppy of grass, pine and lemons, yeasty of leather, apples and toffee.  Flavor has great balance, hoppy grapefruit in flavor dominates with rye in background, finish is hoppy.  Medium bodied creamy and softly carbonated.

Pours Hazy, medium orange with a small off-white head.  Aroma is mightly malty of light bread and cereal, moderatly hoppy, grassy, heavily yeasty; bubblegum, raisins and plums.  Flavor starts well balanced, sweet and grainy at first, finishes a bit more bitter, slight alcohol in the middle, clean finish.  light to medium bodied, oily and livley carbonated. NICE

pours hazy dark amber/orange with a creamy off-white head.  Aroma is moderatly malty like cookies, lightly hoppy and moderatly yeasty of grape and apple.  Flavor starts light but balanced, nice hop flavor, light to medium bodied, creamy and softly carbonated, a bit of alcohol in the finish

Pours clear and medium to dark orange with a large fizzy white head.  Aroma is moderatly malty, lightly hoppy with aromas of allspice, nutmeg, cloves and cinamon.  Flavor starts well balanced and nicly spiced, good hop balance, clove and nutmeg main flavor.  Finishes well balanced.  Medium bodied, creamy and softly carbonated.

Pours sparkling medium orange with a large fizzy off-white head.  Aroma is heavily malty of straw and carmel, lightly hoppy and heavily yeasty of grape, rasins apples and honey.  Flavor stats moderatly sweet and lightly bitter, carmel notes, spice and clove phenols, finishe much the same.  medoum bodied, creamy and livley carbonated.

pours sparkling medium yellow with a large white head. Aroma is lightly malty, heavily hopp of mainly grapefruit.  Flavor starts balanced twords sewwt mainly, with grapefruit hop flavor dominating, finishes much the same, very one dimensional.  light to med bodied, and watery

pours clear and medium orange with a rocky white head.  Aroma is complex, moderatly malty of cookies, grain and carmel, moderatly hoppy of grass and pine, heavily yeasty of barnyard, leather and a hint of soap.  Flavor starts balanced twords the sweet side, fruity yeast flavor, bubble gum and finishes more sweet with a bit of spice.  Medium bodies, creamy and softly carbonated.  I think i like this the best  of the frank zappa series so far.

review_blob: Pours muddy dark black with a small frothy light brown head.  Aroma is moderatly to heavily malty of dark bread, cookies and roasted malts, lightly hoppy and moderatly yeasty of tawny and smoke.  Flavor starts well balanced , roasty, toasty, and nutty, finish is also well balanced, nutty with a nice bitterness.  Medium to fluu bodied, creamy and softly carbonated. Nice!

review_blob: Pours  a sparkling medium amber with a frothy white head.  Aroma is moderatly malty, lightly hoppy and heavily yeasty of barnyard, apple, pineapple and whie wine. pours sparkling medium amber color with a frothy off-white head.  Aroma is lightly malty of light bread and grain, moderatly hoppy of grapefruit and orange, moderatly yeasty, leather and apples.  Flavor is kinda blah. balanced twords the sweet side, lots of crystal finishes the same with a bit of dyacetal.  Light to medium bodied, oily texure coats the mouth and softly carbonated

Light to medium bodied, watery and softly carbonated.   I dont know what the fus is about on this beer.
UPDATED: JUL 31, 2008

pours muddy dark black with a large rocky light brown head.  Aroma is moderatly malty of dark bread , grain and roasted malts.  lightly hoppy of pine and lemons, heavily yeasty , barnyard, grapes, apple and port.  Flavor starts balanced nice roasty flavor on the sweet side with an interesting yeast flavor finishes more sweet but same malt profile.  medium bodied, creamy and fizzy.  Way to much co2 for style.

pours dark red and clear with a frothy light brown head.  Aroma is modratly malty, lightly hoppy and boldly yeasty of bannanna and bubble gum, rasins and cherrys.  Flavor starts balanced twords sweet, dark caramel, cansy, dark fruit, rasins.  Finishes much the same and dry.  Medium bodied, watery and livley

Pours clear dark brown with a large creamy off-white head.  Aroma is moderatly malty of dark bread, roasted malts and carmel lightly hoppy and heavily yeasty of leather, earth, prunes, dates and grapes.  Flavor has a great balance heavy carmel and burnt fruit notes, finish has some spicy notes and balanced twords the sweet side and dark fruit.  medium bodied, creamy and very carbonated.  nice

Nice.

pours muddy black with a large light brown head. Flavor starts lightly sweet but malty / grainy and heavily bitter then finishes ith citrus grapefruit with a long finish.

Pours hazy medium yellow with a frothy off-white head.  Aroma is of grain/straw, leather and earth with pear phenols.  Flavor is well balanced but kinda plain.  Light to med bodied, creamy and softly carbonated.

Flavor however is balanced twards bitter, but way to much alchol HOT alcohol in the flavor, couldnt really pull other flavors out of it.  Medium to full bodied, creamy and softly carbonated.  Heavy Alcohol.
